cs.MA, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CY, cs.AI

The paper deals with the challenges of managing traffic flow in a hybrid vehicular traffic scenario, which involves vehicles with different levels of autonomy sharing the same road network. The proposed system-of-systems model integrates approaches and methods from traffic modeling, data science, and communication engineering to optimize traffic flow. This interdisciplinary nature of the paper suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with managing traffic flow in a heterogeneous environment, which involves multiple agents (vehicles) interacting with each other and the environment. 

cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses data transfer and communication network infrastructure for efficient traffic management. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a system-of-systems model for traffic flow optimization. 

cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but the paper does touch upon the societal impact of autonomous vehicles and the need for efficient traffic management. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper uses simulative optimization methods for traffic flow optimization.
